The paper discusses distributed storage codes and their properties, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and distributed systems (cs.DS) communities. The paper also discusses trade-offs between different code parameters, which is a common topic in coding theory (cs.DC). The paper's focus on repair locality suggests that it may also be relevant to the systems and networking (cs.SI) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories.
